body:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jhOUm3y-oMo

From this video, is possible to conclude that:

 - Stacks are NOT gained or sustained by staying in combat, but rather hitting enemy champions with Basic Attacks or Spells (which includes spells attached to passives like Brand&#039;s), which means that DoT effects like Teemo&#039;s E passive will not extend Conqueror&#039;s duration;

- Stacks are counted for each champion hit, meaning that hitting 5 champions at the same time with &quot;one&quot; basic attack (implies Splash-on-hit effects like Twitch&#039;s Ult and Runaan&#039;s) ~~.....~~ will grant maximum stacks immediately;

- The Healing is not penalized for AoE attacks, probably because it only works against champions, meaning that you cannot just attack minions and other easy access targets for a easy heal;

- The Healing counts the true damage dealt by Conqueror (from my calculations and observations, might be wrong though);
